# Go Service Conventions

- One module (`github.com/ting-boundless/boundless`). Service entrypoints live in
  `go/services/<name>/main.go`; service-private code in `go/services/<name>/internal/`.
- Reuse `pkg/`: `logger`, `identity`, `errs`, `httpx`, `audit`. Don't reinvent.
- Every HTTP service:
  - builds the logger with `logger.New(serviceName, env)`
  - registers `/healthz` + `/readyz` via `httpx.Health`
  - wraps handlers with `httpx.Chain(mux, httpx.RequestID, httpx.Recover, httpx.AccessLog, ...)`
  - returns errors via `errs.Write` (unified envelope), never ad-hoc JSON errors
- `/readyz` probes real dependencies; `/healthz` is liveness only.
- Config from env via `httpx.Env`. No secrets in code.
- Graceful shutdown is handled by `httpx.Server.Run` — use it.
- Keep external dependencies minimal; prefer the standard library.
